  "title": "Lifeguard",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p><p>• Maintain constant surveillance of guests in the facility; act immediately and appropriately to secure safety of guests in the events of emergency<br />• Provide emergency care and treatment as required till the arrival of emergency medical services<br />• Ensure PPE (personal protection equipment) is being used when performing First Aid on guest<br />• Prepare and maintain appropriate incident reports<br />• Present professional appearance and attitude at all times, and maintain a high standard of guest service<br />• Ensure that the Pool Environment is kept clean and well-maintained<br />• Maintain a high standard for the appearance and cleanliness of the pool, the pool deck area, and the turnstiles<br />• Work closely with Pools & Recreation Management team and other related departments to ensure guests’ requests are followed through<br />• Be conversant with closure operations process during inclement weather conditions<br />• Be conversant with all facets of the Pools & Recreation operations including fire safety and emergency related procedures<br />• Monitor activities in the SkyPark and report any suspicious characters, items or/and activities to the Manager<br />• Maintain close liaison with all other Departments to have a good understanding of other Departments’ operational flow, thus ensuring seamless guest experiences</p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u><br /><br />Education & Certification<br /><strong>• Basic lifesaving 1 to 3 certificate</strong><br /><strong>• Bronze Medallion certificate</strong><br /><br />Experience<br />• Prior experience working in hotel or resort is an advantage<br /><br />Other Prerequisites<br />• Willing to work various shifts, including mornings and afternoons, as well as on public holidays<br />• Ability to react calmly and effectively in emergency situations<br />• Skill in the application of lifeguarding surveillance and rescue techniques</p>",
